<span id="freeTextContainer14978266082955554809">Lituma, a Peruvian brigadier, was posted to a small village in the Andes, Naccos. All around lurks the threat of the Shining Path, a terrorist group that regularly executes villagers and travellers. In this tense context, three disappearances took place ...<br/>Lituma in the Andes is a novel with complex construction, which requires a lot of attention from its reader on pain of getting lost in the sequence of scenes. He mixes several narrative threads without clear typographical distinction and the l</span>
  <span id="freeText14978266082955554809" style="display:none">Lituma, a Peruvian brigadier, was posted to a small village in the Andes, Naccos. All around lurks the threat of the Shining Path, a terrorist group that regularly executes villagers and travellers. In this tense context, three disappearances took place ...<br />Lituma in the Andes is a novel with complex construction, which requires a lot of attention from its reader on pain of getting lost in the sequence of scenes. He mixes several narrative threads without clear typographical distinction and the links between the different stories appearing before the end of the work. But it's a well-written book, with an interesting script and characters. For the first reading of Mario Vargas Llosa, it is undeniably a success.</span>
